The Nimzo-Indian Defense:

This is a highly respected and strategic defense against 1.d4, beginning with the moves
1.d4 Nf6
2.c4 e6
3.Nc3 Bb4.

The Nimzo-Indian Defense involves pinning the knight on c3 to control the center and create imbalances.

It's known for its flexibility and the complex strategic play it offers.

The Nimzo-Indian can lead to very different types of positions, depending on the chosen variations and pawn structures.

Some popular lines include the Rubinstein System (e3), the Classical Variation (Qc2), and the Saemisch Variation (f3).